This directory is used to compile and execute all of the automated tests for
OpenSSL. It also contains several utility scripts for making the process of
writing and running tests and other development tools easier. For information
on how to write new unit/automated tests, see:

  http://wiki.openssl.org/index.php/How_To_Write_Unit_Tests_For_OpenSSL

For more information on the unit/automated testing effort in general:

  http://wiki.openssl.org/index.php/Unit_Testing

TEST ENVIRONMENT FOR BASH
-------------------------
test_env.bash contains a handful of environment variables, aliases, and shell
functions to make test development somewhat easier when developing using
the bash shell. To import its contents into your environment:

 $ . test_env.bash

The header comment for test_env.bash contains detailed documentation on its
contents.
